`docs/DECISIONS.md` is the append-only ADR log for the whole project — the rationale-and-rejected-alternatives layer that `intent.md`/rollups never restate. It contains ~53 ADRs, never rewritten in place; corrections are new ADRs that reference and amend earlier ones (e.g. ADR-032 amends ADR-031's overclaim, ADR-052 retires ADR-001/051's "sealed spec" framing).

Load this file only when you need to know *why* something is the way it is, or whether an alternative was already tried and rejected — not for current architecture (that's the rollups) or current invariants (that's `intent.md`). Key structural facts an editor must know before touching project doctrine:

- **Append, never rewrite.** A superseded decision gets a new ADR that says so explicitly (`**Supersedes** [[ADR-NNN]]`); the old entry's text is never edited. Cross-references use `[[ADR-NNN]]` wiki-link syntax.
- **Current live state, reconstructed from the tail:** the cage is a Rust crate (`ctx-cage`, ADR-034) that has evolved into a safety boundary rather than an enforcer (ADR-040) — no broker, no source-masking, RW workspace bind at its *real host path* (ADR-046, not a fixed `/work` alias). Enforcement of "read context before editing" moved from cage-masking to Claude Code hooks (ADR-035/036/037): `ctx-access` was replaced by `ctx-context` (read-only chain printer, no lifecycle/write path).
- **Freshness mechanism is content-hash-based** (ADR-038, "CACT"), not git-diff-based, scoped by `.ctxignore` (seeded once from `.gitignore`, then sole authority — ADR-045), with orphaned mirror artifacts reconciled by `ctx-scan --check/--prune` (ADR-053).
- **`ctx-verify`** is the single agent checkpoint (formats, builds, lints, tests, now also `cargo-machete` — ADR-047); `cargo-deny` and real module-cycle detection are deliberately *not* folded in (both misfire in this offline/toolchain environment).
- **`docs/SPEC.md` no longer exists as a normative doc** — retired to `docs/retired/SPEC.md` (ADR-052); its content is redistributed into config files, prompt files, and this ledger. Don't point new writing at SPEC.md.
- Several ADRs document hard-won debugging war stories with reusable lessons: ADR-024/025 (verification results must be pure functions of git-tracked source, not live build-tree state), ADR-027/042 (a test harness must not be able to corrupt what it verifies), ADR-049 (measure the idle/control case before trusting a load-time profile — a prior root-cause writeup was wrong because it never compared against host baseline).
- When editing this file: append a dated/numbered ADR at the end: **Decision**, **Context/Rationale**, **Rejected** alternatives with reasons. Don't touch earlier entries except to add a superseding note elsewhere.